HEADWORD: Ketol
<hw>Ke"tol</hw> <pr>(k⟦emac⟧"t⟦omac⟧l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Ket</ets>one + ind<ets>ol</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>One of a series of series of complex nitrogenous substances,
represented by methyl ketol and related to indol.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Methyl ketol</b></col>, <cd>a weak organic base, obtained
as a white crystalline substance having the odor of feces.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ketone</ent>⟦br⟧
